<p><strong>In a custom video recording app</strong> using surface the video is rotated 90 degrees clockwise whether played on the device or on the computer (videoplayer and vlc on Ubuntu). Even the thumbnail in Ubuntu file browser is rotated 90 degrees clockwise.</p>  <p><strong>I have already done these</strong></p>  <ul> <li><p>Read up a few StackOverflow questions which say that some players ignore the hint. But all??</p></li> <li><p>Getting the front camera and setting DisplayOrientation and Rotation</p>  <pre><code>private Camera openFrontFacingCamera() {     int cameraCount = 0;     Camera cam = null;     Camera.CameraInfo cameraInfo = new Camera.CameraInfo();     cameraCount = Camera.getNumberOfCameras();      int result = 90;     int degrees = 0;     int rotation = this.getWindowManager().getDefaultDisplay().getRotation();     switch (rotation) {         case Surface.ROTATION_0: degrees = 0; break;         case Surface.ROTATION_90: degrees = 90; break;         case Surface.ROTATION_180: degrees = 180; break;         case Surface.ROTATION_270: degrees = 270; break;     }     for (int camIdx = 0; camIdx&lt;cameraCount; camIdx++) {         Camera.getCameraInfo(camIdx, cameraInfo);         if (cameraInfo.facing == Camera.CameraInfo.CAMERA_FACING_FRONT) {             try {                 cam = Camera.open(camIdx);             } catch (RuntimeException e) {                 Log.e("Your_TAG", "Camera failed to open: " + e.getLocalizedMessage());             }             Log.d(TAG, "degrees: " + String.valueOf(degrees));             result = (cameraInfo.orientation + degrees) % 360;             result = (360 - result) % 360;  // compensate the mirror         }     }     Log.d(TAG, "resultant rotation: " + String.valueOf(result));     cam.setDisplayOrientation(result);      Camera.Parameters params = cam.getParameters();     params.setRotation(360-result);     cam.setParameters(params);      return cam; } </code></pre></li> <li><p>Set the OrientationHint of the media recorder before calling prepare()</p>  <p><code>recorder.setOrientationHint(180);</code></p></li> </ul>